PREAMBLE

The Luanet Protection License (LPL) exists to protect the integrity, security, and originality of the Luanet ecosystem.

Unlike open source licenses, this License is designed to prevent unauthorized copying, redistribution, modification, reverse engineering, and misuse of protected Luanet software and related resources.

All intellectual property rights remain exclusively with Luanet and its respective copyright holders.

---

TERMS AND CONDITIONS

1. Definitions

Software refers to all source code, object code, scripts, documentation, assets, libraries, modules, configurations, loaders, Flow components, Dynamic Components, APIs, and any files distributed as part of a Luanet project.

Protected Components refer to any files marked as protected, obfuscated, encrypted, compiled, or otherwise designated by Luanet.

User refers to any individual or organization using the Software.

---

2. Permitted Use

You may:

- Use the Software for personal or authorized commercial purposes.
- Install the Software on your own systems.
- Configure settings that are explicitly documented as configurable.
- Use official APIs and supported extensions.

No ownership of the Software is transferred to you.

---

3. Restrictions

Unless expressly authorized in writing by Luanet, you may NOT:

- Copy protected source code.
- Steal any portion of the Software.
- Redistribute the Software.
- Re-upload official releases.
- Sell copies of the Software.
- Remove copyright notices.
- Claim the Software as your own work.
- Reverse engineer protected components.
- Deobfuscate protected files.
- Crack licensing or authentication systems.
- Bypass security mechanisms.
- Inject malicious code into official releases.
- Modify protected source files.
- Modify protected configuration files.
- Modify protected loaders.
- Modify protected Dynamic Components.
- Create unauthorized forks.
- Use the Software for illegal purposes.

---

4. Protected Components

Only files specifically designated as configurable may be modified.

Protected Components must remain exactly as distributed.

Any modification of protected files automatically terminates your rights under this License.

---

5. Anti-Skidding Policy

Copying substantial portions of the Software for another project without prior written permission is strictly prohibited.

This includes:

- Copying source code.
- Copying project structures.
- Copying internal algorithms.
- Copying loaders.
- Copying Flow Components.
- Copying Dynamic Components.
- Copying security systems.
- Removing attribution.

